msg_en: Right at the bottom of the ladder, there was a switch on the wall in front of us.
Above it was a plate that read Go... it looked like the rest had been scratched away with a coin.
It was probably a hint...
`Saya@Haha...
`Riki@What's wrong, Saya?
`Saya@These characters are...
`Saya@Saya!? You're leaving off the honorific now!?
`Riki@Well, when I say Saya-san it makes it feel like we're old... you know what I mean?
`Saya@That's not for you to decide...
`Riki@Really? It seemed like a good time.
`Saya@Could you not single-handedly decide when is a good time? And can you even take responsibility!?
`Riki@All I did was leave off the honorific... I don't know what you mean by taking responsibility.
`Saya@Doing something like that is a very special privilege.
`Riki@You are special.
`Saya@That's right. I'm a world-class spy.
`Saya@The only one who can leave off the honorific is, how should I should say it... a true partner... no, a different kind of partner.
`Riki@Okay, I'll wait a little longer.
`Saya@It's not a matter of time...
`Saya@Ah, whatever. Just call me Saya.
`Riki@What? So I'm already that other kind of partner?
`Saya@Gaaaaaaaaaaah!!
`Saya@Do you actually know what you're saying!? Or are you just messing with me!? Well!? Which is it!? Can you take responsibility at that age!? Are you going to!?
`Riki@Don't get so upset! If your hair flies around that much, it'll get ruffled.
`Riki@And what do you mean by responsibility?
`Saya@Kyogeeeeeeee!!
`Riki@Ah, girls shouldn't say things like that.
`Saya@If you're just going to toy with me, I'll say whatever I want, fungaaaa!!
`Riki@There, there.
He was comforting me...
`Saya@Okay, Riki-kun. Calm down and listen.
`Riki@I've been calm.
Right at the bottom of the ladder, there was a switch on the wall in front of us.
Above it was a plate that read Go... it looked like the rest had been scratched away with a coin.
As expected, no hints.
`Saya@Haha...
`Riki@What's wrong, Saya?
That's right. He called me that here.
`Saya@What?
`Riki@Huh, that didn't faze you... that's unexpected...
`Saya@What's wrong?
`Riki@Just now I called you Saya. It took a lot of courage...
`Saya@I can imagine.
`Riki@I should have put the -san on the end...
`Saya@But it makes it feel like we're old, right?
`Riki@Wow, how did you know!? That's what I was just thinking....
`Saya@Later you'll say, No way, let's go together, or even better, I'll go ahead.
`Riki@Haha, if I really end up saying that, you have some awesome precognitive abilities.
`Saya@Awesome spies have them, since we're awesome.
`Riki@No, I don't think being awesome makes you a psychic.
`Saya@Well, umm...
`Saya@Riki-kun. calm down and listen...
`Riki@Okay... what is it?
Right at the bottom of the ladder, there was a switch on the wall in front of us.
Above it was a plate that read Go... it looked like the rest had been scratched away with a coin.
As expected, no hints.
`Saya@From now on, call me Saya.
`Riki@What!? I was just about to muster the courage to say that!
`Riki@How did you know!?
`Saya@I'm psychic.
`Riki@Really!?
`Saya@An awesome spy can read a person's heart.
`Riki@Eh, that's embarrassing! Don't read it right now! I've got a lot on my mind....
`Saya@Don't worry. I'm not going to invade your privacy.
`Riki@Oh, thank god...
`Riki@Wait, didn't you just invade it!?
`Saya@Hey, Riki-kun. This isn't the time to be saying stuff like that.
`Saya@Riki-kun, calm down and listen.
`Riki@Okay... what is it?
It was the same hint-less room.
`Saya@Riki-kun, from now on call me Saya.
`Riki@What!? I was just about to muster the courage to say that!
`Saya@I am psychic. Awesome spies can read people's hearts. But don't worry, I won't invade your privacy. And don't respond with But isn't this an invasion of privacy!?
`Riki@Incredible... you said exactly what I was thinking...
`Saya@This isn't the time to be saying stuff like that. Ready, Riki-kun?
`Riki@Okay... what is it?
`Saya@On this floor there are sensors in every corridor that check whether you've passed through or not.
`Riki@Wow, it's amazing you figured that out right away.
`Saya@If we take the wrong route, we won't be able to reach the ladder.
`Riki@Will it be in the shape of something like on the last floor?
`Saya@Probably. But the hint was scratched out.
`Riki@Oh, yeah. It's bad if we don't have any hints.
It wasn't an 8 or a 5...
I really shouldn't have been the one trying to figure this out.
I decided to leave this to Riki-kun.
`Saya@So, Riki-kun.
Hmm...
I crossed my arms and looked at the switch again.
I nodded ambiguously.
What was I doing...
At any rate, was in the shape of a 5.
I wondered if it was still an 8, like last time...
I nodded ambiguously.
What was I doing...
At any rate, it was in the shape of an 8.
Those marks after the Go...
The scratches had no rhyme or reason.
Think$dAsk Riki-kun's opinion
Hmm...
There was no way to trace Go along the path...
Was there a way to read what was under the scratches...
But it's completely destroyed... maybe if I traced it with my finger...
Go, go...
Ah...
Wait, wasn't that Japanese for 5!?
But if that was true, it could also be part of an 8...
No, it might not work since we'd be passing through the same spot twice...
What if I walked through in the shape of a 5 and then waited to see what would happen?
It was worth a shot!
`Saya@Riki-kun, we're off.
`Riki@Oh, you had an idea. As expected of a spy.
`Saya@Please, don't raise the bar for me...
`Riki@No, no, that's not what I meant... let's just go and if we fail we can think of something else.
...But I would die every time we do.
`Saya@Anything from you?
`Riki@No, there's nothing I can suggest to a pro like you...
Oh well. I'd have to figure it out myself...
`Saya@It's true that I'm a pro, but what I want to hear is your opinion.
`Riki@I really don't think I should have a say here...
`Saya@You're in charge of this kind of work.
`Riki@Um, I guess...
`Saya@You are. That's why I want you to just lay whatever you're thinking out there.
`Riki@Hmm...
He crossed his arms and started staring at the Go on the wall.
`Riki@Don't these scratch marks have some kind of meaning?
`Saya@Such as?
`Riki@The shape. Couldn't it mean 'go in a zig-zag?'
His suggestion intrigued me, so I walked up to the wall.
`Saya@Well... there are cracks in the wall. I could easily blow them up with a bit of explosives.
I laid explosive on the wall.
Just a little bit in two cracks should be okay.
Even though I was running out, I kept unwinding the ignition chord.
*Bam.*
Amidst the cloud of dust, I put a handkerchief over my mouth and stood in awe at what I saw.
`Saya@...A hidden path.
`Riki@And it goes southwest. That's the start of the zig-zag shape.
`Saya@Good job, Riki-kun! I love you!
Crap.
`Saya@Takin' a shit!
`Riki@Ah, are you trying to even things out again?
`Saya@Yeah, that's right.
`Riki@I'm not so sure about a girl saying takin' a shit...
`Saya@What!? Are you saying it's a minus on the scale?
`Riki@Yeah...
`Saya@Then what should I do with the shit!?
`Riki@No, I'm not sure that's what you should be changing...
`Saya@Then, the takin'!? What am I supposed to take...
`Riki@No, I think it's fine if you don't take anything...
`Saya@But then I'm just an embarrassing girl!
`Riki@What's wrong with that?
`Saya@Everything.
`Riki@Those were honest words, so it's okay. I'm really happy.
`Saya@About everything?
`Riki@Well, maybe...
`Saya@Hmm... Something still bugs me, but whatever...
`Saya@Low kick!
*Whack.*
`Riki@Oww... that hurt a little...
Crap, I pointlessly hurt Riki-kun to hide my embarrassment again!!
`Saya@Sorry...
`Riki@No, I'm fine...
`Riki@You aren't doing this for no reason, right?
`Saya@No... not really...
I just can't calm down after saying something like that...
If I was always going to lash out in embarrassment, my days with Riki-kun would leave him battered and bruised...
`Riki@Regardless, looks like this was the right way.
`Saya@Ah, yeah, we found a hidden path!!
`Riki@Isn't that what's important...
It was as if I was just some girl in love! What happened to being a world-class spy... what a mess...
`Saya@Let's go...
`Riki@You don't sound excited...
I headed for the next room and went through the broken wall.
We found ourselves in a new room.
`Saya@So this place is next...
I found it right away.
I put the explosives on the wall.
*Bam!*
Amidst the cloud of dust, I put a handkerchief over my mouth and slipped through the newly made hole.
`Saya@So we aren't using the corridors at all. Just this zig-zag. We keep going like we're cutting up the map.
`Riki@After activating the sensors, we can't go in any direction.
`Saya@There's one weak point in the rooms. The cracks.
`Saya@Even if we don't use explosives, we could probably break them with a good kick.
As I spoke, I destroyed another wall.
I continued to blow up more walls.
I was running low on explosives.
I was trying to conserve as much as I could, but this is going to be difficult.
*Bam!*
To the next room.
`Saya@This is the last room...
*Clunk.*
`Saya@That sound means we were right.
The middle of the floor rose up.
As though a lid had opened, the staircase down appeared.
We had finally reached the 8th floor...
That was the floor where I ran into that guy.
A person who shouldn't have been was there.
I know because I shouldn't have been here, either.
`Riki@Want to rest a little?
`Saya@Good idea.
When he said it, I finally noticed that I was exhausted from the constant tension.
We leaned against a wall and sat down.
I rolled up my sleeve and checked the time on my watch.
It was already morning.
`Riki@It's morning already...
Riki-kun said the same thing.
`Riki@I'm tired...
`Riki@But it's not like we can come back and finish tomorrow...
`Saya@Yeah...
`Saya@Hey, Riki-kun...
`Riki@Yeah?
`Saya@Do you think...
`Saya@...you'll always like me?
`Riki@Eeeh...!?
Maybe that was too straight-forward.
`Riki@You... knew...?
`Saya@Yeah. You've been found out.
`Riki@You got me...
`Riki@That's right, these feelings won't change...
Riki-kun has fallen in love with me every time.  That made me happy.
`Saya@I promise... I'll take you on one, Riki-kun.
`Riki@Huh? What?
On a date.
Saying that would have been unladylike. But he would definitely understand.
`Riki@I don't really get it... but when we aren't busy with all this fighting... it'll be peaceful and fun...
He understood.
I rehydrated myself and stood up.
Gripping my gun, I turned off the light.
All right, onto the decisive battle.
I pushed the button and activated the floor's sensors.
`Saya@I'm going ahead. You come after I've confirmed that it's safe.
`Riki@No way, let's go together, or even better, I'll go ahead.
`Riki@Woah, I actually said it!?
`Saya@Right?
`Riki@Saya, that's incredible! Do you actually have precognitive abilities!?
`Saya@I'm awesome.
`Riki@Yeah, you really are an awesome spy!
`Saya@It sounds like you didn't think so until now.
`Riki@Yeah... sorry, I didn't.
`Saya@It doesn't matter what you think. I'm going, okay?
`Riki@Hold on! I told you I'm not letting you go ahead!
`Saya@Did you forget about my sixth sense?
`Riki@No, I remember, but...
`Saya@If you make a mistake and set off a trap, I could get caught in it too. So sorry, but no.
`Saya@Understand?
`Riki@Yeah...
A dejected response.
I went anyway, not caring.
But I didn't like that grotesque trap... It cut my body to pieces...
Even so, there was nothing to be gained by simply waiting here.
All I could do was hit start and look for a way...
`Saya@Did you forget about my sixth sense?
`Riki@No, I remember, but...
`Saya@If you make a mistake and set off a trap, I could get caught in it too. So sorry, but no.
`Saya@Understand?

`Saya@But then I'd just be an embarrassing teenage girl...

`Saya@Well... if Riki-kun says so, I'll take that back...

`Saya@Okay... taken back.
Ah, that was so embarrassing...
I was totally out of it...
`Saya@Kick!
*Thwack.*
I kneed Riki-kun in the gut.
`Riki@Ugh...
He fell to his knees and didn't move.
Crap...
I said something cheesy, so I did something crazy in an attempt to make things even again but ended up seriously injuring my beloved Riki-kun!
`Saya@Waaaaaaaah...
`Riki@Oww... the pain finally subsided...
`Riki@What was that about? Did you save me from something?
`Saya@W-w-waaaaaaah...

`Saya@W-w-waaaaaaah...
`Riki@No, it's fine, don't cry. See, I'm fine. Totally okay. It might have been good for my liver.
`Saya@Really...?
`Riki@Yes, really. It can break down alcohol much more efficiently now. Not that I can drink yet.
`Saya@...Sorry.
`Riki@You're cute when you worry.
`Saya@Uppercut!
*Bam.*
I knocked him out this time!!
I repeatedly drew circles on the ground with my finger while I waited for him to recover...
`Saya@Sorry...
`Riki@No, it's fine. I feel like my jaw is stronger now. Like I could chew anything.
`Saya@Okay, I'm going, so you follow behind.
We finally started.
I decided to stop with the poop jokes.

But I didn't hear the telltale sound of the floor opening...
When I turned around...
Beams appeared and rushed toward me.

Even if I jumped or laid prone, I wouldn't be able to avoid them.
The lasers cut my body to pieces.
Red beams appeared from the walls.
You've got to be kidding me...
But it felt good, so it was okay.
`Saya@That makes a 5!
`Saya@Well...
But I didn't hear the telltale sound of the floor opening...

Woah, I screwed up!

Was I dying on purpose?

Was I a masochist?
`Saya@Alright, lasers come on!
*Slash*slash*slash!*
I'm going to die now, but that last moment when I was still conscious...
Was the greatest feeling ever...
